== ᱟᱠᱴᱤᱝ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ==
ᱱᱚᱜᱽᱢᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ ᱛᱮᱭᱟᱜ, ᱡᱮᱢᱚᱱ ᱦᱤᱱᱫᱤ, ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ, ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞᱤ, ᱵᱷᱚᱡᱲᱯᱩᱨᱤ, ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱭᱚᱞᱚᱢ, ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱰᱰᱟ, ᱯᱚᱧᱡᱟᱵᱤ, ᱵᱟᱝᱞᱟ, ᱟᱨ ᱢᱚᱨᱟᱴᱷᱤ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱠᱚᱨᱮ ᱠᱟᱹᱢᱤ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱼᱟ ᱾

== ᱨᱟᱡᱽᱱᱤᱛᱤ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ==
It was reported that [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] (BJP), wanted to field Nagma as a candidate from Hyderabad for the 2004 General Lok Sabha Elections.<ref name=Yahoo/><ref>{{cite web|title="Nagma in poll fray?" Times News Network (21 March 2004)|url=http://www1.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/msid-572591,prtpage-1.cms|work=timesofindia.com|access-date=12 April 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222101204/http://www1.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/msid-572591,prtpage-1.cms|archive-date=22 December 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref> But she decided to join Congress in 2004 and campaigned in Andhra Pradesh.
She cited Congress Party's "commitment towards secularism and welfare of the poor and weaker sections" as her reason for joining.<ref name=Yahoo>{{cite web|title="Film actress Nagma joins Congress" Indo-Asian News Service (16 April 2004)|url=http://in.news.yahoo.com/040416/43/2cla9.html|work=Yahoo.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060506072028/http://in.news.yahoo.com/040416/43/2cla9.html|archivedate=6 May 2006}}</ref>  Later, after joining the Congress, Nagma has reportedly said that she first supported the Congress Party because of her admiration for [[Rajiv Gandhi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicindiaonline.com/n/i/telugu/211/|title=See, e.g., "Government office for Nagma?" (10 Nov. 2006) at|publisher=|access-date=31 March 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070528141507/http://www.musicindiaonline.com/n/i/telugu/211/|archive-date=28 May 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref>

She contested 2014 Lok Sabha elections from [[Meerut (Lok Sabha constituency) | Meerut]] as Congress candidate, but came a distant fourth with less than 5% votes and lost her deposit.  

In a 2006 interview, she made a direct link between her family history and her political activism: "My mom is Muslim and my dad is Hindu. We were brought up to respect all religions. Communal riots pained me. I wanted to do something. So I joined politics.". She had to turn down an offer to run for India's [[Lok Sabha]] in 2003 due to her many film commitments. "If I wanted to become a member of Parliament I would need to give 100 per cent to my constituency&nbsp;— which I could not at that point of time."<ref>A Ganesh Nadar interview with Nagma, "Nagma, the survivor&nbsp;— The actress who has truly done it all." (10 March 2006), at rediff.com [http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/09sld3.htm] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090703175816/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/09sld3.htm |date=3 July 2009 }}</ref> In an interview with the ''Hindustan Times'' in 2007, she said "politics will continue".<ref name="You need" />

=== Meerut incident ===
While campaigning for Congress in the Jali Kothi area, a small region in Meerut, Nagma slapped a fellow Congress supporter for getting too close and groping her.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/elections-news/congress-candidate-nagma-slaps-man-who-allegedly-groped-her-at-public-meeting-555421|title=Congress candidate Nagma slaps man who allegedly groped her at public meeting|website=NDTV.com|accessdate=25 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404142901/https://www.ndtv.com/elections-news/congress-candidate-nagma-slaps-man-who-allegedly-groped-her-at-public-meeting-555421|archive-date=4 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>

== ᱱᱤᱡᱚᱨ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ==
Nagma is a convert to Christianity. She has said she always had seen Jesus as a guiding force in her life but only later made the decision to convert, with her biological father's death and her own bout with illness cited as moments that opened her up to the possibility.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://godreports.com/2018/06/bollywood-actress-nagma-discovered-the-uniqueness-of-jesus/|title=Bollywood actress Nagma discovered the uniqueness of Jesus {{!}} God Reports|last=Rodriguez|first=Elio|date=|website=God Reports|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216200641/https://godreports.com/2018/06/bollywood-actress-nagma-discovered-the-uniqueness-of-jesus/|archive-date=16 February 2020|access-date=16 February 2020}}</ref> In 2013 she and fellow actor [[Johnny Lever]] were in the news for promoting Christianity at a Mumbai train station and buses and received threats from [[Hindu nationalist]] groups.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Cinema/2013-12-12/Nagma-in-trouble-over-religious-conversion/79244|title=Nagma In Trouble Over Religious Conversion|date=12 December 2013|website=Hans India|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216200643/https://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Cinema/2013-12-12/Nagma-in-trouble-over-religious-conversion/79244|archive-date=16 February 2020|access-date=}}</ref>

